# Non-Functional Requirements

## Overview

This document defines the non-functional requirements for FlowDesk. These requirements specify the quality attributes and operational standards that the system must meet to ensure a secure, reliable, scalable, and user-friendly experience.

---

# 1. Performance

### NFR-001
The system shall load dashboard pages within 3 seconds under normal operating conditions.

### NFR-002
The system shall support multiple users accessing the platform simultaneously without noticeable performance degradation.

### NFR-003
The system shall process booking requests within 2 seconds under normal network conditions.

### NFR-004
The system shall optimise database queries to minimise response times.

---

# 2. Availability

### NFR-005
The system shall be available 99.5% of the time, excluding scheduled maintenance.

### NFR-006
The system shall recover gracefully from unexpected failures where possible.

---

# 3. Reliability

### NFR-007
The system shall maintain data integrity during normal operation.

### NFR-008
The system shall prevent duplicate bookings.

### NFR-009
The system shall save all successful transactions without data loss.

---

# 4. Security

### NFR-010
User passwords shall be securely encrypted before being stored.

### NFR-011
The system shall enforce secure user authentication.

### NFR-012
The system shall implement role-based access control.

### NFR-013
The system shall protect against common web security vulnerabilities such as SQL Injection and Cross-Site Scripting (XSS).

### NFR-014
The system shall automatically log users out after a period of inactivity.

### NFR-015
Sensitive information shall only be transmitted over secure HTTPS connections.

---

# 5. Usability

### NFR-016
The system shall provide a clean and intuitive user interface.

### NFR-017
Users shall be able to complete common tasks with minimal training.

### NFR-018
Navigation shall remain consistent throughout the application.

### NFR-019
The system shall provide clear validation messages when incorrect information is entered.

### NFR-020
The interface shall follow responsive design principles.

---

# 6. Compatibility

### NFR-021
The system shall support the latest versions of Google Chrome, Microsoft Edge, Mozilla Firefox, and Safari.

### NFR-022
The application shall function correctly on desktop, tablet, and mobile devices.

---

# 7. Scalability

### NFR-023
The system architecture shall support future feature expansion.

### NFR-024
The system shall support an increasing number of businesses and users without major architectural changes.

### NFR-025
The database shall support future growth while maintaining acceptable performance.

---

# 8. Maintainability

### NFR-026
The system shall follow a modular architecture to simplify maintenance.

### NFR-027
Source code shall follow consistent coding standards.

### NFR-028
The application shall be documented to support future development.

### NFR-029
The system shall use version control for source code management.

---

# 9. Data Management

### NFR-030
The system shall validate all user input before storing data.

### NFR-031
The database shall maintain referential integrity between related records.

### NFR-032
The system shall prevent duplicate customer and booking records where applicable.

---

# 10. Accessibility

### NFR-033
The application shall use readable fonts and sufficient colour contrast.

### NFR-034
The interface shall support keyboard navigation where practical.

### NFR-035
Images shall include descriptive alternative text where appropriate.

---

# 11. Backup and Recovery

### NFR-036
Business data shall be backed up regularly.

### NFR-037
The system shall allow restoration of backed-up data in the event of data loss.

---

# 12. Logging and Monitoring

### NFR-038
The system shall record significant application events for troubleshooting purposes.

### NFR-039
The system shall log authentication attempts.

### NFR-040
The system shall log system errors for diagnostic purposes.

---

# 13. Future Requirements

### NFR-041
The platform shall support cloud deployment.

### NFR-042
The system shall support third-party integrations through REST APIs.

### NFR-043
The platform shall support multiple languages in future releases.

### NFR-044
The application shall support horizontal scaling as the user base grows.

### NFR-045
The platform shall support continuous deployment and automated updates.
